[Hillsborough,

December, 1888.] State v. Joseph A. Morin & a. R. M. Wallace, solicitor, for the state. Sulloway Sf Topliff and G. B. Ereneh, for the defendants. Bingham, J.

The case in its present form presents questions *668which may never arise on a trial. It is not advisable to pass upon unnecessary cases. State v. Stevens, 36 N. H. 59, 60; Sceva v. True, 53 N. H. 627; State v. Baron, 64 N. H. 612.

Clark, J., did not sit: the others concurred.

Case discharged.
